Product Deets mentioned on screen!⬆️ 

This teal blue Kajal has a deeper tone, which makes it super versatile. It’s not too bright, so it complements a wide range of skin tones beautifully!

The formula’s super creamy and packed with pigment. It goes on really smoothly, so you don’t need to keep swiping to get that bold color.

It takes about 30–40 seconds to fully set, and once it does; no smudging, no transferring. It stays put all day!

Shade Deets are mentioned on screen!⬆️ 

I’ve tried 3-4 jelly tints before this one, and to be honest, they didn’t work well; either too patchy or uneven color payoff. But this one applies like a dream! It blends out so nicely, doesn’t feel sticky, and lasts a good while too.

Note: Apply it with your fingers or a brush to blend it out. Try not to swipe it directly onto your face, as it can leave a strong stain that’s hard to remove.

What I asked for‼️👇🏻

Ask your stylist for long layers with soft, face-framing strands starting at the chin!
Request feathered or texturized ends for a light, bouncy finish!
Mention you want volume without losing length.
Finish with a smooth round-brush blowout for a soft, polished look!
